{{DISPLAYTITLE:<span style="font-family:Martian Mono; text-shadow: 3px 3px 3px black; color: white;">Level 655: "Bathroom Break"</span>}}{{Alt Class|ent=1|env=1|ext=2|noname=2|no=655}}
{{Underline|00ffcf}}
<span style="text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px black; color: white;>'''Level 655''' is the 656th level of the Backrooms.

==<span style="font-family:Martian Mono; text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px black; color: white;"> Description </span>==
{{Blurimage|file=BathroomBackroom.jpg|caption=A public bathroom in Level 655.}}
<span style="text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px black; color: white;>'''Level 655''', otherwise known as "'''Bathroom Break'''," is an expansive complex of typical public bathrooms, estimated to be 2000 square kilometers (1242 square miles) wide. Level 655 is comprised of tile floors, with inconsistent wall composition between tile, drywall, or drop-ceiling.  The bathrooms are filled with appliances such as toilets, toilet paper, plungers, sinks, air dryers, soap dispensers, etc. The level is quite humid, being set to a predictable 80-90% humidity at all times. The level's temperature on the other hand, is chilly, only being about 11° Celsius (52° Fahrenheit). On Level 655, no bathrooms are exactly the same as one another. 
{{Blurimage|file=Bathall.webp|caption=A hallway connecting different bathrooms.|bg-align=left}}
<span style="text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px black; color: white;>Level 655's bathrooms are connected by a labyrinth of hallways, similar to the ones someone might see before entering a public restroom. In these areas, common things to find are water fountains filled with [[Object 1|Almond Water]], gender signs, potted plants, carpets of various colors, and trash cans.  These hallways connect in strange, confusing ways, making the level notoriously difficult to navigate. The fluorescent lights present in the level emit a hum-buzz similarly to [[Level 0]] but is much less loud or violent. What is audibly noticeable is the music that plays throughout speakers in the level. The music can be soft, or mind-numbingly loud at random intervals. The music is unrecognizable, and if there are lyrics, they are incoherent, but the music seems to be set and styled around the early American 1900's with little variability. 
{{Blurimage|file=Pitstop.png|caption=A claustrophobic bathroom.|bg-align=right}}
<span style="text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px black; color: white;>In the hallways of the level, you can find janitorial closets with cleaning supplies, hardware tools, and even mini fridges stocked with food. The food is completely random, but most importantly edible, and has been described as extremely mild in taste. One could potentially live well in Level 655, ignoring the encounters with entities. While the janitorial closets are usually quite small, sometimes they can be as big as one of the bathrooms. These large closets house electrical appliances which can be altered to toggle power in nearby rooms.<br />

{{Blurimage|file=BathroomComplex2.jpg|caption=Yet another image of a bathroom in Level 655.}}
<span style="text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px black; color: white;>Level 655's general structure is densely packed, with very few empty spaces in the level. The level has little to no regard for uniformity. There are several rooms that appear to be lopsided, empty, or differed in colors. Sometimes the running water in the level fails to function, or the bathrooms seems to be more reminiscent of a private bathroom. The further you go from your original position, the more often these anomalies will happen. It seems to have little effect on entity count, however.

<span style="text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px black; color: white;>The stalls in the level, despite the lock being flimsy in the [[The Frontrooms|Frontrooms]], are actually incredibly sturdy. These stalls can act as a hiding place or even a good place to sleep, because you are mostly safe from entities there. Entities (for the most part) cannot fit underneath or above the door. Other useful hiding places can be the janitorial closets as mentioned earlier, or inside of access doors. The level, thanks to the abundance of these hiding places, is an optimal place for sanctuary if needed.

==<span style="font-family:Martian Mono; text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px black; color: white;"> Special Rooms </span>==
{{Blurimage|file=BathroomComplexShowers.jpg|caption=The shower room. Photographer status unknown.}}

<span style="text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px black; color: white;>There are a few special rooms in the level.
===<span style="font-family:Martian Mono; text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px black; color: white;">Shower Rooms </span>===
<span style="text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px black; color: white;>The shower rooms are square rooms made strictly of tile with showers placed along two walls. These rooms share the same architecture as the rest of the level but are almost always fully made of tile. These showers are constantly on and set to the hottest temperature, at 35° Celsius (95° Fahrenheit). Some showers can shoot out Cashew Water, which are deadly if stepped in. The rooms are chock-full of seemingly random objects. These rooms are helpful checkpoints to any wanderers who are lucky enough to find them.
===<span style="font-family:Martian Mono; text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px black; color: white;">Saunas </span>===
<span style="text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px black; color: white;>This level is also harbors the saunas. These rooms are a combination of hot tubs, bathtubs, and saunas. They are noticeably much hotter and more humid than any other places in the level. Saunas are always filled with hot steam, regardless of if they were used recently. These rooms do not follow the architectural pattern of the rest of the level. They resemble a modern bathroom design, adopting an extremely cramped and claustrophobic interior.
<br>
<br>

==<span style="font-family:Martian Mono; text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px black; color: white;"> Entities </span>==
<span style="text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px black; color: white;>The entities on this level are few and far between. Below is a list of confirmed entities. 

* <span style="text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px black; color: white;>[[Entity 4|Deathmoths]]: Female Deathmoths are quite common on the level. They are attracted to light, so just staying out of vicinity should be enough to stay safe from these. If not, dark spots will do just fine for hiding from them.
* <span style="text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px black; color: white;>[[Entity 5|Clumps]]: Clumps can be found under sinks, in cubbies, or in stalls. They are relatively smaller than the Clumps on most other levels and are far less lethal. Nonetheless, they are still dangerous, so react quickly if you believe you are near a Clump.
* <span style="text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px black; color: white;>[[Entity 10|Skin-Stealers]]: They are extremely uncommon on this level, but two confirmed cases of them have been reported. They are the easiest to repel by blockading yourself in a stall.
* <span style="text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px black; color: white;>[[Hydrolitis Plague]]: They are extremely common on this level. It is notably in the toilets and rarely in the shower water.
* <span style="text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px black; color: white;>[[Entity 36|Lighters]]: The Lighters on level 655, even though they pay no mind to wanderers, are still the deadliest entity on the level, since hiding is mostly useless because of their heat, but they can be easily outrun if needed. 
{{Underline|00ffcf}}<span style="text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px black; color: white;">As previously stated, stalls, janitorial closets, and other dark hiding places make a great way to escape majority of the entities listed, and the ones that are not stopped by them can be outflanked or aren't as aggressive as on other levels. 

==<span style="font-family:Martian Mono; text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px black; color: white;"> Colonies and Outposts </span>==
<span style="text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px black; color: white;>Even though, in theory, colonies would be possible, the level's size makes it difficult to start one. None exist at this time.

==<span style="font-family:Martian Mono; text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px black; color: white;"> Entrances and Exits </span>==


===<span style="font-family:Martian Mono;text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px black; color: white;"> Entrances </span>===

* <span style="text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px black; color: white;>In many levels that take place indoors, there is a high chance to find a door labeled "Bathroom." This door leads to Level 655. Because of its frequency, Level 655 has many people going in and out at all times.
* <span style="text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px black; color: white;>You can no-clip into a sink in [[Level 156]].
* <span style="text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px black; color: white;>Before the first wave, digging a hole on the beach in [[Level 255]] occasionally would bring wanderers here.

===<span style="font-family:Martian Mono;text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px black; color: white;"> Exits </span>===

*<span style="text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px black; color: white;>Finding hallways that lead to doors with labels can lead most commonly to [[Level 5]], [[Level 20]], Level 156, or [[Level 330]] depending on what the labels say.
*<span style="text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px black; color: white;>Wandering for too long in the ceiling space will lead to [[Level 28]].
*<span style="text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px black; color: white;>Finding advertisement posters and noclipping through them can lead to [[Level 877]].
